# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# YOUR PERSONAL JOB SEARCH DATA — NEVER COMMITTED, NEVER PUBLISHED
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Everything in private/ is YOUR data:
# - career-narrative.md     Your real story, targets, deal-breakers
# - tracker.md              Your application log and funnel analysis
# - watchlist.md            Your custom company list and filters
# - jobs/                   Your search history and verdicts
#   - digest-*.md           Scans you've reviewed
#   - verdicts.json         Your AI collaborator's judgments
#   - dismissed.json        Postings you rejected (with reasons)
#   - learnings.md          Accumulated dismissal patterns
#   - postings/             Individual JD analyses
#
# The .gitignore rule below says:
#   - Ignore EVERYTHING in private/ (your data stays private)
#   - EXCEPT private/README.md (the template for forks to read)
#
# This means: if you fork this repo and push to GitHub, your search data
# never leaves your machine. The public repo has only examples.

private/*
!private/README.md

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OS AND TOOL NOISE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# NOTE: .gitignore does NOT support inline (end-of-line) comments —
# put each comment on its own line, or the pattern won't match.

# macOS metadata
.DS_Store
# Windows metadata
Thumbs.db
# Python bytecode, compiled files, virtual env, packaging
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
*.egg-info/

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# EDITOR AND IDE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# VS Code settings (you customize locally)
.vscode/
# JetBrains IDE
.idea/
# Vim swap files
*.swp
*.swo
# Emacs backups
*~

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL: IF YOU MODIFY THE SCRAPER TO WRITE ELSEWHERE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

output/                    # Legacy output dir (deprecated, use private/jobs/)
*.csv                      # Exports (keep in private/ instead)

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECURITY: NEVER COMMIT CREDENTIALS OR SECRETS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

.env                       # Environment variables
.env.local                 # Local overrides
secrets/                   # Credentials folder
*.key                      # SSH keys
*.pem                      # Certificates

# API keys for optional sources live in private/ (already gitignored above,
# but listed explicitly here as documentation of what might exist):
# private/usajobs.env       — USAJobs API key (free, from developer.usajobs.gov)
